org.apache.olingo.server.api.uri

Interface UriInfoResource

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    UriInfo

    public interface UriInfoResource
    Used for URI info kind UriInfoKind.resource to describe URIs like E.g. http://.../serviceroot/entitySet

      • getUriResourceParts

        List<UriResource> getUriResourceParts()
        The path segments behind the service root define which resources are requested by that URI. This may be entities/functions/actions and more. Each segments information (name, key predicates, function parameters, ...) is stored within an resource object dedicated for that segment type.

        For example: the URI http://.../serviceroot/entitySet(1)/Adresse will have 2 ResourceParts:
        - The first one of type UriResourceEntitySet containing the name of the entity set and also the key predicate information.
        - The second one of type UriResourceComplexProperty containing the name of the accessed complex property
        Returns:
        List of resource parts.
